    <article id="section-card-content">
      <h1 class="app-article-headline hca-typography--headline">Content</h1>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Cards provide context and an entry point to more robust information and views. Their content and quantity can vary greatly. Cards within a card collection can each contain a unique data set, such as a checklist with an action.</p>

              <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: Don't overload cards with extraneous information or actions.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Content hierarchy</h4>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Use hierarchy within the card to direct users’ attention to the most important information. For example, place primary content at the top of the card, or use typography to emphasize primary content.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Images can reinforce other content in a card. Quality and contextual imagery conveys emotion and builds trust with users. However, their size and placement within the card depends on whether images are the primary content or are being used to supplement other content on the card.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-1">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/content-intro.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="" />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption"></figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Background images</h4>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Text is most legible when placed on a solid color background with a sufficient contrast ratio to the text. Text placed on image backgrounds should preserve text legibility.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--do">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/text-on-image-do.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Preserve text legibility by leveraging color overlays on an image." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Preserve text legibility by leveraging color overlays on an image.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--dont">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/text-on-image-dont.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Using full contrast images skews the legibility of text, and makes it difficult to read." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Using full contrast images skews the legibility of text, and makes it difficult to read.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="hca-typography--title">Content Blocks</h2>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Cards can be constructed using blocks of content that include:
                <ul class="app-list app-list--bulleted">
                  <li class="app-list__item">Title/subheader block</li>
                  <li class="app-list__item">Rich media block</li>
                  <li class="app-list__item">Content/supplemental content block</li>
                  <li class="app-list__item">Action bar</li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">These blocks can be organized in many ways to present different types of content.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-2">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/content-blocks-small-card.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="" />
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-4">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/content-blocks-media-title.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="" />
            </figure>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-4">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/content-blocks-map.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="" />
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
    </article>
