    <article id="section-card-behavior">
      <h1 class="app-article-headline hca-typography--headline">Behavior</h1>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Cards can have a responsive width and variable height.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: Cards do not flip over to reveal information on the back.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Supported Gestures</h4>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Card gestures should be consistently implemented within a card collection.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The swipe gesture may be used on a per-card basis. Limit swipe gestures within a view so that they don’t overlap with one another. For example, a swipeable card should not contain a swipeable image carousel, so that only a single action occurs when the card is swiped.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The pick-up-and-move gesture may be used if it is important for the user to be able to sort cards within a collection, but consider if filtering or sorting would better organize the content.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Card collection filtering and sorting</h4>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Card collections can be programmatically sorted or filtered by date, file size, alphabetical order, or other parameters.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The first item in the collection is positioned at the top left.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The order proceeds left to right and top to bottom.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/card-sort-order.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Sort order for cards" />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Card sort order from left to right, top to bottom</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="hca-typography--title">Card focus</h2>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">When traversing through focus points on a card, all focusable elements are visited before moving to the next card.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">For interfaces that depend on focus traversal for navigation (D-pad and keyboard), cards should have either a primary action or open a new view containing primary and supplemental actions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-4">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/primary-action-focused.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Example of focus traversal on a card" />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Primary action selected during focus traversal</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/dropdown-focus-expand.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Expanded supporting text made visible, with the focus then placed on a supplemental action." />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Expanded supporting text made visible, with the focus then placed on a supplemental action.</figcaption>
          </figure>
          </div>
        </div>




    </article>
    {{!-- / Behavior Article --}}


    <hr />

    <article id="section-card-actions">
      <h1 class="app-article-headline hca-typography--headline">Actions</h1>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The primary action in a card is typically the card itself.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Supplemental actions can vary from card to card in a collection, depending on the content type and expected outcome; for example, playing a video versus expanding collapsed content. Position actions consistently within cards that are a part of a collection.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Supplemental Actions</h4>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Supplemental actions within the card are explicitly called out using icons, text, and UI controls. They are typically placed at the bottom of the card.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Limit supplemental actions to two actions, in addition to an overflow menu.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-2">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/single-action-card.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="A card whose action area is the entire card itself" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">A card whose action area is the entire card itself</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/double-action-card.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="A card whose action area is the entire card itself" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">A card with two action areas</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="hca-typography--title">UI Controls</h2>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">UI controls, like a slider, placed inline with primary content can modify the view of the primary content. For example, a slider to choose an amount, stars to rate content, or a segmented button to select a date range.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-2">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/ui-controls.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Example of UI controls within a card" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">A card containing UI controls among the primary content.</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="hca-typography--title">Additional Actions</h2>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Cards can make use of the overflow (or "more") menu icon to support additional actions related to the content of the card.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-7">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/overflow-menu-card.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Example of UI controls within a card" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">A card utilizing an overflow menu for supplemental actions</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Remember that cards serve as a quick entry point to more information. This means that cards need to avoid presenting too many actions or links to a user. Card content should not contain inline links to other content, rather, they should provide one or two main actions that lead the user to more detailed content.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-2">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--dont">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/cards/card-actions-dont.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Example of UI controls within a card" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Cards should avoid inline links among their content. This removes focus from the primary action(s).</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

    </article>
    {{!-- / Actions Article --}}



